column33: Thomas loves water and is motivated by water activities. He responds well to routine and repetition, which can help him adapt to the structure of swimming lessons. He also has a keen interest in sensory input, and playing in the water is something that excites and engages him.  His interests include exploring different textures and sensations in the water and playing with floating toys.
column34: Thomas is highly motivated by sensory experiences, especially water play, which makes the pool environment naturally engaging for him.  He responds well to positive reinforcement, such as verbal praise and enthusiastic encouragement.  Clapping and shouting can help reinforce his achievements and encourage him to keep trying.  He also enjoys interactive toys, particularly those that light up or make sounds, so incorporating floating toys or water-friendly sensory items can be beneficial.  Additionally, allowing him to explore the water at his own pace while gradually introducing new skills can support his engagement and positive behavior.
